---
import ServicePage from '../../components/ServicePage.astro';
---
<ServicePage
	title="in Clapham"
	highlight="Lift (Weight Training) Club"
	heroSubtitle="Build strength, confidence, and resilience through structured coaching in a supportive, small-group setting."
	breadcrumb="Lift (Weight Training) Club"
	seoTitle="Lift (Weight Training) Club in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Coached weight training in Clapham. Small-group strength sessions that bridge rehabilitation and independent training, progressive and tailored to you."
	intro={[
		"Our Weight Training Club provides a supportive, coached environment to learn and develop strength safely. It is designed to bridge the gap between rehabilitation and independent training, helping you build the foundations for long-term health and performance.",
		"Whether you are completely new to lifting or looking to refine your technique, sessions are structured, progressive, and tailored within a small group setting.",
		"Strength training is a key component of maintaining muscle mass, bone health, and overall physical resilience.",
	]}
	whenHeading="When to consider"
	whenHighlight="joining"
	whenIntro="You may benefit from the Weight Training Club if you:"
	whenList={[
		"Want to learn how to lift safely and effectively",
		"Feel unsure about technique (e.g. squat, hinge, press)",
		"Have stopped progressing with independent training",
		"Have seen the research into the health benefits of lifting",
		"Are returning to strength training after injury",
		"Want a structured and consistent approach to training",
	]}
	howHeading="How the"
	howHighlight="club works"
	howIntro="Sessions follow a structured programme designed to build strength progressively. You will:"
	howList={[
		"Learn the fundamental movement patterns: push, pull, squat, and hinge",
		"Train using barbells and other resistance equipment",
		"Receive coaching on technique and positioning",
		"Progress load and complexity over time",
		"Train in a small group with individual guidance",
		"Have fun!",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoIntro="The club is designed to be inclusive and accessible. No prior experience is required."
	whoList={[
		"Beginners learning lifting technique from the ground up",
		"Postnatal and prenatal clients training safely with appropriate modifications",
		"Individuals with previous injuries returning to strength in a controlled environment",
		"Our veterans maintaining and increasing muscle mass, bone density, and function",
		"Regular gym users seeking structure and coaching to progress further",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Do I need experience to join?", a: "No. The club is beginner-friendly and coached throughout." },
		{ q: "Will I get individual attention in a group setting?", a: "Yes. Group sizes are kept small to allow for coaching and feedback." },
		{ q: "Can I join if I\\'ve had back pain?", a: "Yes. Sessions are delivered within a clinical setting and can be adapted as needed. Alex is also an apprentice physiotherapist, so you\\'re in good hands." },
		{ q: "What is a progressive programme?", a: "A structured plan where exercises and loads are gradually increased over time to build strength safely." },
		{ q: "Can I train during pregnancy?", a: "Yes. Exercises can be adapted appropriately. Best to call and chat to us first." },
	]}
/>
